"script": "Add up the growth of every hair on your head, and your hair grows about seven miles every single year. That's longer than a hundred football fields, sprouting straight out of your scalp annually. You see, the average head holds around 100,000 strands, and each one stretches roughly half an inch a month. And over a lifetime, your scalp spins out enough hair to reach from New York to London and back again. So sitting on top of your head is a slow-motion factory, quietly producing miles of thread that you trim away and toss in the bin.",
